Author: Gaurav Gosain <itsgauravgosain@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Jul 18 20:47:11 2026 +0400

    test(vt): fuzz the emulator's parsers
    
    Feeds arbitrary byte streams to the emulator and asserts the invariants
    a multiplexer depends on: parsing never panics, returns within a budget,
    never changes the screen dimensions the host configured, leaves the
    cursor inside the screen, and retains bounded heap.
    
    The chunked target writes the same input one byte at a time and requires
    the rendered screen to match, since a PTY read boundary can land
    anywhere. The resize target interleaves parsing with resizes.
    
    Seeds are drawn from sequences real programs emit plus the hostile
    shapes a review flagged: unbounded repeat counts, oversized graphics
    payloads, guest file and shm transfers, zlib payloads, unterminated
    accumulators and truncated introducers.

